com.wookler.zconfig.common.model

Class ConfigPropertiesNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wookler.zconfig.common.model.AbstractConfigNode
      • com.wookler.zconfig.common.model.ConfigElementNode
        • com.wookler.zconfig.common.model.ConfigKeyValueNode
          • com.wookler.zconfig.common.model.ConfigPropertiesNode

  • public class ConfigPropertiesNode
extends ConfigKeyValueNode
    Configuration node representing configuration properties. Properties can be defined for any path scope and used as substitutions markers when specifying configuration values. Properties are specified as key/value pairs enclosed in a {properties} block. Example: JSON >> 
         properties: {
         key1: value1,
         key2: value2,
         ...
     }
    XML >> 
         
         
         
         ...
